Rainstorm destroyed 271 residential houses in 7 Communities of Sanga local Government Area of Kaduna State. The Council boss, Mr. Charles Danladi disclosed this while briefing Newsmen over the weekend in Kafanchan. Danladi said the late Wednesday night heavy rain fall came with a devastating wind which blew off the roofs of 271 houses including a one block of classroom in Sabon Gida. He disclosed that the areas worse hit are Janda, Bera, Ungwan Goma, Zac Zawan, Hayin Dam, Aboro and Sabon Gida Communities. According to him, he directed the council department of works to carry out an extensive assessment of the damages in order to prepare a report that will be sent to SEMA in particular to come and give them some relief. ” Some houses were completely destroyed I really felt for my people, adding am putting modalities to see how we can give them emergency relief to see they dont suffer alot in this raining season. He added that a woman sustain injuries as a result of the heavy downpour but responding to treatment in one of the hospital in the area. He however called on the people in area to comply with Government stay-at-home order and observed the social distancing as Mallam Nasir el-Rufai administration is working out measures to reach out to the downtrodden,” Charles added. A victim, Simon Dauda who was interviewed by LEADERSHIP expressed shock over the incident, describing it as the worst in the past 5 years. He appealed to the relevant agencies to come to their aid to help cushion the effect of the tragedy as they’re in raining season already. Another victim, Hamisu Ibrahim from Sabon Gida said the disaster came at a time when people are grappling to contain the Coronavirus pandemic and no money at hand, hence the need for State Emergency Management Agency to urgently assist them. 